        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>89</offset>
        <text>Functional redundancy in bacterial communities is expected to allow microbial assemblages to survive perturbation by allowing continuity in function despite compositional changes in communities.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>284</offset>
        <text>Recent evidence suggests, however, that microbial communities change both composition and function as a result of disturbance.
</text>
